# Orka — AI-Powered Semantic Code Surgery

Orka is installed as an **editable pip package** in this project's virtual environment.

## CLI Commands

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `orka scan` | Scan the codebase, build dependency graph + vector embeddings |
| `orka inspect --id <node>` | Inspect a graph node and its connections |
| `orka extract --file <path> --cls <Class> --dest <path>` | Extract a class into a new file; auto-heal imports |
| `orka refactor --file <path> --cls <Class> --method <method> --req "<req>" [--provider <provider>]` | Surgically refactor a method body using AI |

## Quick Start

```bash
# Scan the codebase first
orka scan

# Refactor a method
orka refactor --file src/app.py --cls MyService --method handle_order --req "add validation"

# Extract a class
orka extract --file src/utils.py --cls OldClass --dest src/models/old_class.py

# Inspect dependencies
orka inspect --id "Class:myproject.models.User"
```

## Supported Providers

OpenAI, DeepSeek, Together AI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter, Groq — set via `.env`.

## Architecture

- **OrkaGraphDB** — NetworkX dependency graph of all files, classes, methods, imports
- **OrkaVectorDB** — ChromaDB semantic search over source code
- **MethodBodyReplacer** — LibCST-based surgical patching (preserves signatures, decorators)
- **TransplantTransformer** — Class extraction with auto-import-healing
- **ImportCascadeTransformer** — Auto-updates imports across all dependent files
